parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Dashboard and Airbag Deployment Concerns
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked dashboard can cause the airbag to deploy improperly, potentially leading to serious injury or death to passengers.
symptoms: Cracked dashboard
airbag deployment concerns
sharp objects may fly into the face of passengers
and distraction while driving due to rattling and shaking dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall and Unavailability of Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Takata airbag recall has left many vehicles with potentially deadly airbags, and the unavailability of parts has delayed the repair process, putting passengers at risk.
symptoms: Notification of Takata airbag recall
unavailability of parts
and delayed repair process.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in an accident
and the vehicle was severely damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked dashboard can pose a safety hazard in the event of an accident, as sharp edges or flying debris can cause injury to occupants. Additionally, the cracked dashboard can compromise the airbag's functionality, leading to malfunction or failure.
symptoms: Cracks on the dashboard
often near the airbag compartment or instrument cluster
which can spread and worsen over time. In some cases
chunks of the dashboard may fall out
exposing underlying mechanical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can lead to a potentially hazardous situation if the airbag deploys, causing sharp plastic shards to fly into the passenger compartment, potentially injuring occupants.
symptoms: Cracks appear on the dashboard
often around the airbag module
and can spread over time
causing the dashboard to sink or fall apart. In some cases
papers or objects placed on the dashboard may fall into the cracks
and the sharp edges can cause cuts or injuries.
